cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with object pose estimation in depth images, which is a core problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely sub-category as object pose estimation is an important task in robotics for object manipulation and grasping. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a novel part-based architecture that uses privileged one-class learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper addresses the challenges of intra-class variations and distribution shifts, which are important problems in AI. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on graphics or rendering, but rather on object pose estimation in depth images.
